HEADWORD: Cautionary block
<hw>Cau"tion*a*ry block</hw>. <fld>(Railroads)</fld> <def>A block in
which two or more trains are permitted to travel, under restrictions
imposed by a caution card or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cautioner</ent>⟦br⟧
